text:
The Ba Chor Mee is super good, although is slightly more expensive ($5) for residential coffee shop environment but I feel itâ€™s worth the price.

The store opens daily till 7pm. Rest on Wednesday
Nice outdoor seating area. Mala grilled fish is not bad, price is really affordable.
The 1st Tea they gave me, saw the milk has curdled. Told the staff and they say nothing wrong, but will change for me. The new cup looks normal no more curb, but taste horrible, very diluted.
Personal prefer roasted delights and Chinese mixed rice. Both offer good variety and value for meal food choice.

Beware of Hong Man Tian stall as shown in photo which not only occupies/ reserves tables meant for patrons but is also unhygienic - aside from not wearing mask properly despite not eating or drinking, good luck unless you enjoy some foot smell to go along with your food.
